## -------- RR (banking crises panel) --------
uk_years_rr <- RR %>%
  filter(Year >= 1816, Year <= 1913, Country == "United Kingdom") %>%
  distinct(Year)

df_RR <- uk_years_rr %>%
  mutate(Country = "United Kingdom", Crisis = 1L) %>%
  left_join(
    RR %>%
      filter(Year >= 1816, Year <= 1913) %>%
      group_by(Year) %>%
      summarise(
        n_countries_crisis = n_distinct(Country),
        countries_in_crisis = paste(sort(unique(Country)), collapse = ", "),
        .groups = "drop"
      ),
    by = "Year"
  ) %>%
  arrange(Year)
cr_cols <- c("Banking.Crisis","Systemic.Crisis","Currency.Crises","Inflation.Crises")

GCD2 <- GCD %>%
  filter(Year >= 1816, Year <= 1913) %>%
  mutate(across(all_of(cr_cols), ~ as.integer(.x > 0)),
         any_crisis = as.integer(rowSums(across(all_of(cr_cols))) > 0))

uk_gcd <- GCD2 %>%
  filter(Country == "United Kingdom", any_crisis == 1L) %>%
  arrange(Year)

df_GCD <- uk_gcd %>%
  left_join(
    GCD2 %>%
      filter(Year %in% uk_gcd$Year, any_crisis == 1L) %>%
      group_by(Year) %>%
      summarise(
        n_countries_any_crisis = n_distinct(Country),
        countries_in_crisis = paste(sort(unique(Country)), collapse = ", "),
        .groups = "drop"
      ),
    by = "Year"
  )

war_crisis <- war %>%
  # First filter to your desired time range
  filter(year >= 1816, year <= 1913) %>%
  # Then create complete country-year combinations
  complete(iso3, year = 1816:1913) %>%
  mutate(
    flag_RR   = as.integer(year %in% df_RR$Year),
    flag_GCD  = as.integer(year %in% df_GCD$Year),
    # Impute 0 for missing war status
    across(c(is_inter, is_intra), ~ ifelse(is.na(.), 0, .)),
    at_war = as.integer(is_inter == 1 | is_intra == 1)
  )
# --- cross-section --- 
war_crisis_cs <- war_crisis %>%
  group_by(iso3) %>%
  summarise(
    yr_war   = sum(at_war,       na.rm = TRUE),
    yr_inter = sum(is_inter,  na.rm = TRUE),
    yr_intra = sum(is_intra,  na.rm = TRUE),
    yr_homeland = sum(homeland,  na.rm = TRUE),

    yr_in_crisis_RR        = sum(at_war      & flag_RR  == 1L, na.rm = TRUE),
    yr_in_crisis_RR_inter  = sum(is_inter & flag_RR  == 1L, na.rm = TRUE),
    yr_in_crisis_RR_intra  = sum(is_intra & flag_RR  == 1L, na.rm = TRUE),

    yr_in_crisis_GCD       = sum(at_war      & flag_GCD == 1L, na.rm = TRUE),
    yr_in_crisis_GCD_inter = sum(is_inter & flag_GCD == 1L, na.rm = TRUE),
    yr_in_crisis_GCD_intra = sum(is_intra & flag_GCD == 1L, na.rm = TRUE),
    .groups = "drop"
  )
# Impute 0 for missing values
war_crisis_cs[is.na(war_crisis_cs)] <- 0

## ---- Helpers ---------------------------------------------------------------
detect_binary_cols <- function(df) {
  df <- as.data.frame(df)
  vapply(df, function(z) is.numeric(z) && all(na.omit(z) %in% c(0,1)), logical(1)) |> 
    {\(idx) names(df)[idx]}()
}

## ---- NO-WAR spec -----------------------------------------------------------
X_nowar <- df0[, feat_nowar, drop = FALSE] |> as.data.frame()
rownames(X_nowar) <- df0$country
stopifnot(!anyNA(X_nowar))

bin_cols_nowar <- detect_binary_cols(X_nowar)

# FAMD: binaries as factors
Xf_nowar <- X_nowar
if (length(bin_cols_nowar)) {
  Xf_nowar[bin_cols_nowar] <- lapply(Xf_nowar[bin_cols_nowar], function(x) factor(x, levels = c(0,1)))
}

famd_nowar <- FactoMineR::FAMD(Xf_nowar, ncp = max(2, min(10, ncol(Xf_nowar)-1)), graph = FALSE)
perc_nowar <- famd_nowar$eig[,2]
dopt_nowar <- which(cumsum(perc_nowar) >= 80)[1]
if (is.na(dopt_nowar)) dopt_nowar <- min(2, ncol(famd_nowar$ind$coord))
S_nowar <- famd_nowar$ind$coord[, 1:dopt_nowar, drop = FALSE]

k_grid <- 2:8
distS_nowar <- dist(S_nowar)
sil_vals_FAMD_nowar <- numeric(length(k_grid))
km_models_nowar <- vector("list", length(k_grid))
for (i in seq_along(k_grid)) {
  k <- k_grid[i]
  km <- kmeans(S_nowar, centers = k, nstart = 50)
  km_models_nowar[[i]] <- km
  sil_vals_FAMD_nowar[i] <- if (length(unique(km$cluster)) >= 2)
    mean(silhouette(as.integer(km$cluster), distS_nowar)[,3]) else NA_real_
}
best_i_FAMD_nowar <- which.max(sil_vals_FAMD_nowar)
km_best_nowar <- km_models_nowar[[best_i_FAMD_nowar]]
cl_FAMD_nowar <- factor(km_best_nowar$cluster)
sil_FAMD_nowar <- sil_vals_FAMD_nowar[best_i_FAMD_nowar]
k_FAMD_nowar <- nlevels(cl_FAMD_nowar)

# --- B) Gower + PAM -------------------------------------------------------------------
# Gower distance (Gower 1971) handles mixed types; we keep binaries numeric 0/1 and declare
# them asymmetric ('asymm') so mismatches on 1's count more than 0-0 matches.
# Weights: set to 2 for war vars (if present), else 1. No imputation.
Xg_nowar <- X_nowar
Xg_nowar[, c(14, 15, 16)] <- lapply(Xg_nowar[, c(14, 15, 16)], factor)
w_nowar <- setNames(rep(1, ncol(Xg_nowar)), colnames(Xg_nowar))
war_names_nowar <- intersect(vars_war, colnames(Xg_nowar))  # empty by design in NO_WAR spec
if (length(war_names_nowar)) w_nowar[war_names_nowar] <- 2

Dg_nowar <- cluster::daisy(Xg_nowar, metric = "gower",
                           weights = w_nowar[colnames(Xg_nowar)],
                           type = if (length(bin_cols_nowar)) list(asymm = bin_cols_nowar) else NULL)
## Warning in cluster::daisy(Xg_nowar, metric = "gower", weights =
## w_nowar[colnames(Xg_nowar)], : binary variable(s) 13 treated as interval scaled
# PAM (Kaufman & Rousseeuw 1990) on Gower dissimilarities. k chosen by silhouette over 2..8.
sil_vals_PAM_nowar <- numeric(length(k_grid))
pam_models_nowar <- vector("list", length(k_grid))
for (i in seq_along(k_grid)) {
  k <- k_grid[i]
  fit <- pam(Dg_nowar, k, diss = TRUE)
  pam_models_nowar[[i]] <- fit
  sil_vals_PAM_nowar[i] <- fit$silinfo$avg.width
}
best_i_PAM_nowar <- which.max(sil_vals_PAM_nowar)
pam_best_nowar <- pam_models_nowar[[best_i_PAM_nowar]]
cl_PAM_nowar <- factor(pam_best_nowar$clustering)       # INTERPRETATION: cluster labels from Gower+PAM
sil_PAM_nowar <- pam_best_nowar$silinfo$avg.width       # INTERPRETATION: PAMs average silhouette
k_PAM_nowar <- length(unique(cl_PAM_nowar))

# Plot a world map for a given clustering (expects columns iso3c, cluster)
plot_cluster_map <- function(df_map, title) {
  world <- rnaturalearth::ne_countries(scale = "medium", returnclass = "sf") |>
    sf::st_transform(4326) |>
    dplyr::select(iso_a3, geometry)

  gdat <- world |>
    dplyr::left_join(df_map |> mutate(cluster = factor(cluster)), by = c("iso_a3" = "iso3c"))

  ggplot2::ggplot(gdat) +
    ggplot2::geom_sf(aes(fill = cluster), color = "white", size = 0.15) +
    ggplot2::scale_fill_brewer(palette = "Set2", na.value = "grey90", name = "Cluster") +
    ggplot2::labs(title = title, x = NULL, y = NULL) +
    ggplot2::theme_void(base_size = 12) +
    ggplot2::theme(
      plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, face = "bold"),
      legend.position = "bottom",
      legend.key.height = unit(4, "mm")
    )
}

##    country cowcode iso3c cluster_with cluster_nowar changed
## 19   China     710   CHN            1             2    TRUE
## 27 Denmark     390   DNK            2             1    TRUE
plot_change_map <- function(df_change, title) {
  library(sf)
  library(dplyr)
  library(ggplot2)
  library(ggrepel)
  library(rnaturalearth)
  library(rnaturalearthdata)

  # Compute whether cluster changed
  df_change <- df_change |>
    mutate(changed = cluster_with != cluster_nowar)

  # Base world map
  world <- ne_countries(scale = "medium", returnclass = "sf") |>
    st_transform(4326) |>
    select(iso_a3, geometry)

  # Merge and assign fill colors
  gdat <- world |>
    left_join(df_change, by = c("iso_a3" = "iso3c")) |>
    mutate(
      fill_color = case_when(
        changed ~ "changed",
        cluster_with == 1 ~ "cluster1",
        cluster_with == 2 ~ "cluster2"
      )
    )

  # Centroids for changed countries
  changed_centroids <- gdat |>
    filter(changed & !st_is_empty(geometry)) |>
    st_centroid() |>
    mutate(
      lon = st_coordinates(geometry)[,1],
      lat = st_coordinates(geometry)[,2]
    )

  # Plot
  ggplot() +
    # Base layer for countries without data
    geom_sf(data = gdat |> filter(is.na(fill_color)),
            fill = "grey90", color = "white", size = 0.1) +
    # Filled layer for clustered countries
    geom_sf(data = gdat |> filter(!is.na(fill_color)),
            aes(fill = fill_color), color = "white", size = 0.15) +
    scale_fill_manual(
      values = c(
        "cluster1" = "#1f78b4",  # lighter blue
        "cluster2" = "#023e8a",  # darker blue
        "changed"  = "#d73027"   # red
      ),
      labels = c(
        "cluster1" = "Advanced Fiscal States",
        "cluster2" = "Developing Fiscal States",
        "changed"  = "Changed"
      ),
      name = NULL,
      guide = guide_legend(override.aes = list(color = NA))
    ) +
    geom_label_repel(
      data = changed_centroids,
      aes(x = lon, y = lat, label = iso_a3),
      size = 3.2,
      fontface = "bold",
      color = "black",
      fill = "white",
      label.size = 0.4,
      label.r = unit(0.15, "lines"),
      box.padding = 0.35,
      point.padding = 0.25,
      segment.color = NA,
      seed = 1234
    ) +
    labs(title = title, x = NULL, y = NULL) +
    theme_void(base_size = 12) +
    theme(
      plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, face = "bold"),
      legend.position = "bottom",
      legend.key.height = unit(4, "mm")
    )
}
pc1 <- plot_change_map(cluster_comparison, "Cluster Status by State Features (FAMD)")

  ggplot(aes(x = factor(cluster_label,
                        levels = c("Developing Fiscal States", "Advanced Fiscal States")),
             y = avg_pit_95_05)) +
  geom_boxplot(aes(color = cluster_label),
               fill = "white", outlier.shape = NA, linewidth = 0.8) +
  geom_jitter(
    aes(color = ifelse(changed, "Changed", cluster_label),
        size = changed),
    width = 0.15, alpha = 0.9
  ) +
  scale_color_manual(
    values = c(
      "Developing Fiscal States" = "#023e8a",
      "Advanced Fiscal States"   = "#1f78b4",
      "Changed"                  = "red"
    )
  ) +
  scale_size_manual(values = c(`TRUE` = 2, `FALSE` = 1.25), guide = "none") +
  labs(x = NULL, y = "Average PIT (19952005)") +
  facet_wrap(~ .strip) +
  theme_bw(base_size = 13) +
  theme(
    strip.background = element_rect(fill = "grey90", colour = "black"),
    strip.text       = element_text(size = 12, face = "bold"),
    panel.border     = element_rect(color = "black", fill = NA, linewidth = 0.6),
    panel.grid.major = element_line(color = "grey90", linewidth = 0.3),
    panel.grid.minor = element_blank(),

    plot.margin      = margin(1, 1, 1, 1)
  )
